messages.text: Meet me at The End after school?
hey hey Laura, I think I found your note in my bag…is this your new number???
what’s up with the weird handwriting btw??? this is you, right??
hellooooo? donde estás?
Aqui.
…but this isn’t Laura??
omg Carlos. I’m telling Mom
Who’s Carlos?
Wait? What?
It’s not Carlos.
You better tell me who the heck you are creepo or I’m blocking you RIGHT NOW.
Wait. Please don’t block me. I promise I’m not a creep.
prove it
I like you.
Ummmmm. Still creepy.
Meet me tomorrow at The End.
What is THE END???
They say It’s where ghosts from this town go to meet their lost loves.
And if the timing is right, you can sometimes see them around sunset.
Wow. Really?
My neighbor, Mrs. Salas, told me. She’s lived near San Antonio her whole life.
So have I…
Take a right from the parking lot at the back end of school, near the gym. And you’ll need your phone.
It’s the only way I can talk.
What do you mean, it’s the only way you can talk?
I’ll explain more later, but I’m from New York City…
OK??
718. It’s a New York area code. Google it.
I don’t know anyone from New York.
Yeah, you do.
Uh. I think I know who I know.
You do know me. I mean, I hope so.
Dude. Whoever you are. You’re freaking me out.
I’m not trying to scare you. Really.
Then WHO ARE YOU?
Steve.
Steve??? I don’t know anybody named Steve. You’re gonna have to give me more than that.
I’m in Ms. Barker’s homeroom, OK?
I don’t know anybody in that homeroom.
Esteban. That’s my real name. You know Steve/Esteban. Esteban Morales.
Esteban…still don’t know who the heck you are.
Yeah. I was afraid of that.
In Ms. Barker’s homeroom?
Right.
So why should I meet you? Just because you’re in Ms. Barker’s homeroom doesn’t mean you’re not a weirdo.
You can look me up on Facebook.
Would Laura give your number to a weirdo?
I’m starting to seriously doubt our friendship…
I’ll be at The End tomorrow right after school. If you want to come, great. If not, I get it.
I’ll text you when I get there.
the next day
Hey.
hey — can’t stay long! Only a little while before practice.
That’s cool.
I’m glad you came. You look really nice. If there’s anything you want to say, you have to text me.
Unless you speak ASL, which would be really cool.
ASL?
American Sign Language.
Oh…now I know who you are. You’re the new kid. The transplant. The deaf one.
Yeah. I’m all of those things. Guess you do know who I am!
Sorry. That’s probably not PC or something.
It’s okay. That’s how people see me.
yeah… pero, I’m sure you’re a lot of other things, too, right? It’s not a big deal.
I know.
So why did you have me come here?
See the sign?
yeah
Now when you leave here you can say you’ve been to “The End” and back.
You’re a dork.
Guess so.
I didn’t mean it like in a bad way.
It’s cool.
Did you see that?? That light?
No way.
Do you think it was a ghost??
Maybe…
spooky
But also pretty cool, right? Like they found each other again.
yeah
I’m glad you came out here. See? I’m not a weirdo.
Well, I’m not so sure…
kidding ;)
I’ve seen you play soccer before. You’re really good.
Thanks. Do you play?
Not like you.
LOL
Seriously. You could go pro.
maybe
Look! Look!
It must be another one!
I wonder who they were…
Maybe they’ve been here since the Alamo…
LOL
Anyway, better get to practice.
HEY. I was hoping maybe we could see a movie or something sometime.
Yeah…that could be fun. But would it be any fun for you?
I can read lips…
Oh, wow. That’s cool.
I’m not an alien, you know.
I didn’t mean it like that…
Sure.
Really. I just. I’ve never known someone like you before. I’ve gotta learn.
This place is pretty cool. Now that I know you’re not a creep or a weirdo I’ll come to The End whenever you want.
Whenever I want?
Except school, and practice, and everything else.
Okay. That seems fair.
awesome
Awesome.
Hey, Esteban.
Yeah?
Next time, you should really just, like, write me a Facebook message or something. It’d be a lot easier. ;)
Haha. Okay. ☺
